OL,3,C'We have lost our four-year-old boy
OL,4,Cfor a dead person's status symbol'
OL,6,FOn the day he passed away, Eli had
OL,7,Fcelebrated his graduation from nursery.
OL,9,FHe was walking home with his great
OL,10,Fgrandmother through Rawtenstall
OL,11,Fcemetery when the falling stone hit
OL,12,Fhim. They were just minutes from his
OL,13,Fhouse.
OL,15,FHis parents rushed to the cemetery,
OL,16,FJessica in her dressing gown: "When we
OL,17,Fsaw him we just knew. Tom tried to do
OL,18,FCPR for what felt like an eternity.
OL,20,F"It fell on top of him and it did kill
OL,21,Fhim straight away."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/12
