OL,3,C'We have lost our four-year-old boy
OL,4,Cfor a dead person's status symbol'
OL,6,F"I have had to lose my son for
OL,7,Fsomething which could have been
OL,8,Fprevented. Hopefully we can change the
OL,9,Flaw, hopefully we can save lives."
OL,11,FThomas said he hoped any future law
OL,12,Fwould be named 'Eli's Law', in memory
OL,13,Fof him son.
OL,15,F"It would be nice if it had Eli's name
OL,16,Fon it," he said.
OL,18,F"It would mean a lot - just knowing
OL,19,Fthat he is protecting other families
OL,20,Ffrom going from what we've had to go
OL,21,Fthrough."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G8/12
